{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DQBzmtj6ZGC98Y9q8ZX7fN","type":"tool_result","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 8)\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — create-story (2026-03-23T14:50Z)\n\n- **Stale technical notes:** Original story referenced line numbers from before story 9-2. Rewrote to reflect actual current code state.\n- **Files list correction:** Original story listed `src/commands/init.ts` but missed `docs-scaffold.ts`. `init.ts` doesn't need changes; `docs-scaffold.ts` does for `getStackLabel()`.\n- **Risk:** `path` import missing in init-project.ts — per-stack OTLP loop needs `path.join()` but only `basename` is imported.\n- **Observation:** Story 9-2 already did partial work (added `detectStacks` call and stacks population), reducing scope to per-stack iteration loops.\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:55Z)\n\n- **Code quality concern:** Per-stack coverage loop calls `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discards return value — `HarnessState.coverage` only has single `tool` field, not per-stack map. Future addition needed.\n- **Observation:** OTLP per-stack loop assigns `result.otlp` based on matching `detection.stack === stack` (primary stack). Last match wins if duplicates exist.\n- **Observation:** Fallback `if (!result.otlp)` after OTLP loop handles edge case where primary stack isn't in `allStacks`.\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — code-review (2026-03-23T15:02Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Per-stack coverage loop was dead code — called `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discarded all return values\n- **HIGH (fixed):** OTLP `result.otlp` matched by stack name only, wrong detection when multiple subdirs share same stack\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Double filesystem scan — `detectStack()` calls `detectStacks()` internally, then init called it again\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Integration tests mocked `detectStack` but init-project no longer called it after refactor\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` assigned without type interface field existing\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` map persisted but no consumer reads it yet\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `detectAppType` only considers primary root stack in multi-stack projects\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — verify (2026-03-23T15:08Z)\n\n- All 4 ACs passed black-box verification\n- Beads sync failed (story file status line not found) — non-blocking\n- Container cleanup succeeded\n- Observability check: VictoriaMetrics stack was down at start, `codeharness stack start` reported shared stack already running (inconsistent)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 9)\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — create-story (2026-03-23T15:12Z)\n\n- **Workaround:** Overwrote existing skeleton story file (had 3 ACs without verification tags) with full 6-AC story\n- **Risk:** AC4 (validator passes on multi-stage output) depends on dockerfile-validator.ts handling multiple FROM lines — may need validator updates\n- **Risk:** Tech spec says new `generateMultiStackDockerfile()` but epics say update existing function — story opts for backward-compat overload approach\n- **Observation:** All 6 ACs tagged cli-verifiable (unit tests and CLI commands only)\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:16Z)\n\n- **Positive finding:** Validator already handles multi-stage (multiple FROM lines) — no changes needed\n- **Branch coverage 91.17%:** vitest/istanbul artifact with else-if chai