{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VjtqXLdEFg96EvVoMek1sN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XJdxfV2CiivfsxzjZrqE9E","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers-proof.md","old_string":"## AC5: scaffoldDocs passes StackDetection[] to generateAgentsMdContent\n\nThis is verified by AC1. The AGENTS.md generated by `codeharness init` contains per-stack sections (`### Rust (backend/)` and `### Node.js (frontend/)`), which is only possible if `scaffoldDocs()` passed the full `StackDetection[]` array (with directory info) to `generateAgentsMdContent()`. A single-stack string parameter would not produce per-directory sections.\n\n**Evidence:** AGENTS.md has per-stack sections with subdirectory paths — this proves the StackDetection array was passed through scaffoldDocs.\n\n**Verdict:** PASS","new_string":"## AC5: scaffoldDocs passes StackDetection[] to generateAgentsMdContent\n\nThis is verified by AC1. The AGENTS.md generated by `codeharness init` contains per-stack sections, which is only possible if `scaffoldDocs()` passed the full `StackDetection[]` array to `generateAgentsMdContent()`.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/multistack && grep -c \"###\" AGENTS.md'\n```\n\n```output\n2\n```\n\n**Evidence:** AGENTS.md has 2 per-stack sections (`### Rust (backend/)` and `### Node.js (frontend/)`) with subdirectory paths — this proves the StackDetection array was passed through scaffoldDocs. A single-stack string parameter would not produce per-directory sections.\n\n**Verdict:** PASS"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":759,"cache_read_input_tokens":83746,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":759},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inf