{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KVMKeZGY1f8ZWCqqe3d1ow","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n     2→\n     3→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n     6→- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n     7→- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n     9→\n    10→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n    13→- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n    14→- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n    15→- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n    16→\n    17→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n    20→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n    21→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n    22→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n    26→- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 8)\n    31→\n    32→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — create-story (2026-03-23T14:50Z)\n    33→\n    34→- **Stale technical notes:** Original story referenced line numbers from before story 9-2. Rewrote to reflect actual current code state.\n    35→- **Files list correction:** Original story listed `src/commands/init.ts` but missed `docs-scaffold.ts`. `init.ts` doesn't need changes; `docs-scaffold.ts` does for `getStackLabel()`.\n    36→- **Risk:** `path` import missing in init-project.ts — per-stack OTLP loop needs `path.join()` but only `basename` is imported.\n    37→- **Observation:** Story 9-2 already did partial work (added `detectStacks` call and stacks population), reducing scope to per-stack iteration loops.\n    38→\n    39→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:55Z)\n    40→\n    41→- **Code quality concern:** Per-stack coverage loop calls `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discards return value — `HarnessState.coverage` only has single `tool` field, not per-stack map. Future addition needed.\n    42→- **Observation:** OTLP per-stack loop assigns `result.otlp` based on matching `detection.stack === stack` (primary stack). Last match wins if duplicates exist.\n    43→- **Observation:** Fallback `if (!result.otlp)` after OTLP loop handles edge case where primary stack isn't in `allStacks`.\n    44→\n    45→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — code-review (2026-03-23T15:02Z)\n    46→\n    47→- **HIGH (fixed):** Per-stack coverage loop was dead code — called `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discarded all return values\n    48→- **HIGH (fixed):** OTLP `result.otlp` matched by stack name only, wrong detection when multiple subdirs share same stack\n    49→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Double filesystem scan — `detectStack()` calls `detectStacks()` internally, then init called it again\n    50→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Integration tests mocked `detectStack` but init-project no longer called it after refactor\n    51→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` assigned without type interface field existing\n    52→- **LOW (not fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` map persisted but no consumer reads it yet\n    53→- **LOW (not fixed):** `detectAppType` only considers primary root stack in multi-stack projects\n    54→\n    55→### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — verify (2026-03-23T15:08Z)\n    56→\n    57→- All 4 ACs passed black-box verification\n    58→- Beads sync failed (story file status line not found) — non-blocking\n    59→- Container cleanup succeeded\n    60→- Observability check: VictoriaMetrics stack was down at start, `codeharness stack start` reported shared stack already running (inconsistent)\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 9)\n    65→\n    66→### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — create-story (2026-03-23T15:12Z)\n    67→\n    68→- **Workaround:** Overwrote existing skeleton story file (had 3 ACs without verification tags) with full 6-AC story\n    69→- **Risk:** AC4 (validator passes on multi-stage output) depends on dockerfile-validator.ts handling multiple FROM lines — may need validator updates\n    70→- **Risk:** Tech spec says new `generateMultiStackDockerfile()` but epics say update existing function — story opts for backward-compat overload approach\n    71→- **Observation:** All 6 ACs tagged cli-verifiable (unit tests and CLI commands only)\n    72→\n    73→### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:16Z)\n    74→\n    75→- **Positive finding:** Validator already handles multi-stage (multiple FROM lines) — no changes needed\n    76→- **Branch coverage 91.17%:** vitest/istanbul artifact with else-if chains — statement/function/line at 100%\n    77→- **No exec-plan/proof docs created:** Story mentions docs/exec-plans/active/ but dev focused on code+tests only\n    78→- **File growth:** dockerfile-template.ts grew from 149 to 220 lines (under 300-line limit)\n    79→\n    80→### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — code-review (2026-03-23T15:21Z)\n    81→\n    82→- **HIGH (fixed):** Missing Showboat proof document — story claimed done but file didn't exist\n    83→- **HIGH (fixed):** Type inconsistency between DockerfileTemplateResult.stacks (required) and InitResult.dockerfile.stacks (optional)\n    84→- **HIGH (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — didn't reflect new StackDetection[] signature or 5 new helpers\n    85→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unknown stacks in multi-stage array produced malformed Dockerfile with no error\n    86→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Hardcoded python3.12 path in runtimeCopyDirectives — breaks on version change\n    87→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** COPY . . copies entire monorepo into each build stage (wasteful, potential secret leak)\n    88→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** No .dockerignore warning for multi-stage builds\n    89→- **LOW (not fixed):** stacks field naming collision between DockerfileTemplateResult.stacks and InitResult.stacks\n    90→- **LOW (not fixed):** Inconsistent non-root user strategy (node vs nobody)\n    91→- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3131 tests pass.\n    92→\n    93→### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — verify (2026-03-23T15:33Z)\n    94→\n    95→- **Time constraint:** Verification started but session time budget exhausted before verifier could complete\n    96→- **State:** Docker container running, verifier session spawned but still in progress\n    97→- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n    98→\n    99→---\n   100→\n   101→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 10)\n   102→\n   103→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — create-story (2026-03-23T15:41Z)\n   104→\n   105→- **Ambiguity in epic AC4:** Original epic says verify/env.ts uses `stacks.includes('nodejs')` but actual code calls `detectStack()` directly, not state-based. AC rewritten to reflect actual code path.\n   106→- **ACs already satisfied:** AC2 (getStackLabel arrays) and AC3 (getProjectName multi-file) already implemented from story 9-3. Kept as verify-not-reimplement ACs.\n   107→- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` at 229/300 lines, adding multi-stack AGENTS.md generation brings it close to ceiling.\n   108→- **No `readme.test.ts` found:** May need new test file for readme template changes.\n   109→\n   110→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:46Z)\n   111→\n   112→- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` grew from 229 to ~295 lines — under 300 limit but very close. Future extraction needed.\n   113→- **AC text mismatch:** Story AC mentions `npm ci` but template uses `npm install`. Tests match actual template behavior.\n   114→- **Test ripple effect:** ~15 existing verify-env tests needed updating to add `mockDetectStacks` calls due to detection method change.\n   115→- **AC7 logic difference:** AC specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` but implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct (checks anywhere in array).\n   116→\n   117→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — code-review (2026-03-23T15:51Z)\n   118→\n   119→- **HIGH (fixed):** Single-element `StackDetection[]` bypassed single-stack path — direct callers of `generateAgentsMdContent` got wrong format.\n   120→- **HIGH (fixed):** Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate AGENTS.md with no stack info.\n   121→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` instead of install command.\n   122→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Zero test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` with `stacks` option (AC5 gap). Added 2 integration tests.\n   123→- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicated stack-to-label mapping between `getStackLabel()` and `stackDisplayName()`.\n   124→- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify-env.test.ts` still imports/mocks stale `detectStack` (singular).\n   125→- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3153 tests pass.\n   126→\n   127→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T16:04Z)\n   128→\n   129→- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — session time budget exhausted (27/30 min used, <3 min remaining)\n   130→- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n   131→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011uJegr2jyuH8cJvCc5N1MG","session_id":"3e18f278-46ed-484a-b67e-63de3b199291","uuid":"f5afea61-cb1a-437c-a8ad-ec35b6b51c90","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:17:39.995Z"}
