{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Fq7WutubjsF6hBt1CvZMR","type":"tool_result","content":"  2170→1. **Pre-creating skeleton story files** — they go stale fast. Better to create stories on demand.\n  2171→2. **Shipping dead code paths** — dev should verify every code path has a consumer before marking done.\n  2172→3. **Relying on 30-min sessions for stories with 6+ ACs** — stories 9-4 and 9-5 both ran long. Either split larger stories or budget 2 sessions.\n  2173→4. **Duplicate utility functions** — `getStackLabel()` vs `stackDisplayName()` happened because dev didn't search for existing equivalents. Dev should grep before creating helpers.\n  2174→\n  2175→---\n  2176→\n  2177→## 6. Action Items\n  2178→\n  2179→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  2180→\n  2181→- [ ] **Verify story 9-5** — it's the only remaining story in Epic 9. Pick up as Tier C next session.\n  2182→- [ ] **Confirm 9-4 verification proof** — commit exists but verifier may not have written proof doc. Check and re-verify if needed.\n  2183→\n  2184→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  2185→\n  2186→- [ ] **Extract `docs-scaffold.ts`** — at 295/300 lines, one more feature pushes it over. Split into `docs-scaffold.ts` + `agents-md-generator.ts`.\n  2187→- [ ] **Consolidate `getStackLabel()` / `stackDisplayName()`** — pick one, delete the other, update all callers.\n  2188→- [ ] **Clean up `verify-env.test.ts`** — still mocks `detectStack` (singular) which is stale after multi-stack refactor.\n  2189→- [ ] **Add `stacks` field assertions to `init-project.test.ts`** — coverage gap from 9-2.\n  2190→- [ ] **Fix `migrateState()` stack name validation** — casts `raw.stack as StackName` without checking against known names.\n  2191→\n  2192→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  2193→\n  2194→- [ ] **Multi-stack `detectAppType`** — only considers primary root stack. Needs per-subdir app type detection.\n  2195→- [ ] **`state.coverage.tools` consumer** — field is persisted but nothing reads it yet.\n  2196→- [ ] **Reduce double `detectStacks()` calls** in `recoverCorruptedState()` — detection runs twice.\n  2197→- [ ] **Inconsistent non-root user strategy** in Dockerfiles — `node` vs `nobody` depending on stack.\n  2198→- [ ] **`stacks` field naming collision** between `DockerfileTemplateResult.stacks` and `InitResult.stacks` — confusing in the same pipeline.\n  2199→- [ ] **Fix pre-existing type errors** in `bridge.test.ts`, `run.test.ts`, `stack.test.ts`, `status.test.ts`.\n  2200→- [ ] **Investigate beads sync failure** — story file status line not found during 9-3 verify.\n  2201→- [ ] **Investigate VictoriaMetrics stack start inconsistency** — reports \"already running\" when stack is down.\n  2202→- [ ] **Flaky test: `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic`** — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n  2203→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015EqqD48Q9FBPgRJcfQCoEz","session_id":"3e18f278-46ed-484a-b67e-63de3b199291","uuid":"88fac26c-fd40-49f6-af92-d1bbca6921b4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:21:17.550Z"}
